text: Irondequoit () is a town (and census-designated place) in Monroe County, New York, United States. As of the 2020 census, the town-CDP had a population of 51,043. The name is of Iroquois origin and means "where the land meets the water". ==References== Category:Towns in New York (state) Category:Census- designated places in New York (state)
title: Irondequoit, New York
